        contentMd: "# Thyroid Gland - Foundation\n\n## Anatomy Quick Review\n- Butterfly-shaped, overlies 2nd-4th tracheal rings\n- Blood supply: Superior thyroid artery (ECA), Inferior thyroid artery (thyrocervical trunk)\n- **Recurrent laryngeal nerve** at risk during surgery\n\n## Thyroid Hormones\n| Feature | T4 (Thyroxine) | T3 (Triiodothyronine) |\n|---------|----------------|----------------------|\n| Amount secreted | 90% | 10% |\n| Biological activity | Less active | **4x more active** |\n| Half-life | 6-7 days | 1 day |\n| Binding | 99.97% bound | 99.7% bound |\n\n## Iodine Metabolism\n- Daily requirement: **150 mcg** (250 mcg in pregnancy)\n- Trapped by **NIS (Na+/I- Symporter)** — 25:1 ratio\n- Thiocyanate, perchlorate block NIS\n\n## HPT Axis\nHypothalamus → TRH → Pituitary → TSH → Thyroid → T3/T4 (negative feedback)\n\n## Transport\n- **TBG**: 70% of T4\n- Transthyretin: 15%\n- Albumin: 15%\n- Only **free T3/T4** are biologically active",
