        summary: "Hypothyroidism (cretinism, myxedema, Hashimoto) and hyperthyroidism (Graves, thyroid storm) with Indian context.",
        contentMd: "# Clinical Applications\n\n## Hypothyroidism\n### Cretinism\n- Cause: Iodine deficiency (most common worldwide), thyroid dysgenesis\n- Features: Mental retardation, short stature, coarse features, pot belly\n- India: Endemic in sub-Himalayan belt; NIDDCP mandates iodized salt\n\n### Myxedema\n- Non-pitting edema from GAG deposition\n- Weight gain, cold intolerance, bradycardia, delayed ankle jerk\n- **Myxedema coma**: Hypothermia, hypoglycemia, hyponatremia\n\n### Hashimoto Thyroiditis\n- Anti-TPO antibodies, lymphocytic infiltration\n- Most common cause in iodine-sufficient areas\n\n## Hyperthyroidism\n### Graves Disease\n- TSI (Thyroid Stimulating Immunoglobulins) activate TSH receptor\n- Diffuse goiter, exophthalmos, pretibial myxedema\n- TSH is LOW (suppressed)\n\n### Thyroid Storm\n- Treatment order: **PTU → Propranolol → Lugol iodine → Hydrocortisone**\n\n## Thyroid Function Tests\n| Condition | TSH | Free T4 |\n|-----------|-----|--------|\n| Primary hypothyroid | High | Low |\n| Secondary hypothyroid | Low | Low |\n| Graves disease | Low | High |\n| Subclinical hypothyroid | High | Normal |",
