        contentMd: "# Adrenal Gland - Foundation\n\n## Anatomy\n- Retroperitoneal, superior pole of each kidney\n- Right: Triangular; Left: Semilunar\n- Blood supply: Superior (inferior phrenic), Middle (aorta), Inferior (renal artery)\n- Venous: Right → IVC directly; Left → left renal vein\n\n## Adrenal Cortex (Mesoderm origin)\n| Zone | Hormone | Regulation |\n|------|---------|------------|\n| Zona Glomerulosa | **Aldosterone** | RAAS, K+ |\n| Zona Fasciculata | **Cortisol** | ACTH |\n| Zona Reticularis | **Androgens** (DHEA) | ACTH |\n\n## Adrenal Medulla (Neural crest origin)\n- Modified sympathetic ganglion\n- Secretes: **Epinephrine (80%)** and norepinephrine (20%)\n- Enzyme PNMT converts NE → Epi (induced by cortisol)\n\n## Key Enzymes\n- All steroid synthesis starts from **cholesterol → pregnenolone** (by cholesterol desmolase/CYP11A1)\n- Rate-limiting step: Cholesterol → Pregnenolone\n\n> **Clinical Pearl**: Cortisol from zona fasciculata induces PNMT in the medulla. This is why the medulla sits inside the cortex — portal blood carries cortisol directly to medullary cells.",
